The paper deals with the problem of predicting human trajectories and abnormal event detection using deep learning techniques. The paper uses LSTM networks and attention mechanisms to model the trajectory information. The paper also mentions the use of surveillance databases, which suggests that the paper may belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques and attention mechanisms suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of LSTM networks suggests that the paper may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper also mentions the task of abnormal event detection, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the software engineering (cs.SD) sub-category.
